teks yang tersimpan di dalam naskah. Gejala tersebut memperlihatkan bahwa dalam penyalinan naskah teks senantiasa mengalami perubahan sehingga lahirlah wujud teks yang bervariasi. Dengan demikian, adanya variasi-variasi untuk suatu informasi masa lampau yang terkandung dalam naskah itulah yang melahirkan kerja filologi (Baried, 1994). \nMenurut Reynolds (1968) tujuan utama kritik teks adalah mengembalikan sebuah teks sedekat mungkin dengan sumber aslinya. Sebuah teks akan mengalami proses transmisi dan penyalinan berulangkali sehingga menghasilkan perbedaan-perbedaan pada teks turunan. Reynolds juga menjelaskan tahapan yang harus dilakukan dalam pembuatan kritik teks yaitu tahapan resensi yang terdiri dari tiga tahap 1) menganalisa keterkaitan antara teks-teks yang ada 2) mengeliminasi teks yang tidak memiliki nilai eksklusif, dan 3) membuat pohon silsilah atau stemma sebagai pendekatan untuk merekonstruksi teks yang hilang berdasarkan teks yang masih ada. Setelah tahapan resensi, tahapan berikutnya adalah proses kritis dalam mengkaji naskah yang dirasa paling otentik dan melakukan pendekatan berupa emendasi menggunakan tingkat keyakinan dan kriteria tertentu yang dapat dipertanggungjawabkan.\nMakalah ini akan memaparkan mengenai prosedur penelitian filologi dari empat contoh penelitian filologi yaitu Tuhfat al-Nafis (TN), Hikayat Muhammad Hanafiyyah (HMH), Hikayat Sri Rama (HSR), dan Wawacan Sama\u2019un (WS). Beberapa aspek yang menjadi fokus pembahasa antara lain mengenai aspek pernaskahan isu stemma, strategi pemilihan naskah, gejala bahasa dan pendekatan struktur untuk memetakan pola-pola dalam masing-masing teks tersebut.\n", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 66209129, "asset_id": 45957942, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 103415183, "first_name": "Corina", "last_name": "Ilmaniar", "domain_name": "ui", "page_name": "corinailmaniar", "display_name": "Corina H Ilmaniar", "profile_url": "https://ui.academia.edu/corinailmaniar?f_ri=961759", "photo": "/images/s65_no_pic.png"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 1031, "name": "Southeast Asian Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Southeast_Asian_Studies?f_ri=961759", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 162115, "name": "Sastra Indonesia", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Sastra_Indonesia?f_ri=961759", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 961759, "name": "Indonesia and the Malay World", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Indonesia_and_the_Malay_World?f_ri=961759", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 1773964, "name": "Indonesian Islamic Philology", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Indonesian_Islamic_Philology?f_ri=961759", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 1916513, "name": "Malay and Indonesian philology", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malay_and_Indonesian_philology?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 1916515, "name": "Malay and Indonesian literature", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malay_and_Indonesian_literature?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 2165402, "name": "Indonesian Language and Literature", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Indonesian_Language_and_Literature-1?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 2503034, "name": "Indonesian and Malay literature", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Indonesian_and_Malay_literature?f_ri=961759"}]}, {"id": 37952673, "title": "Constituting (fe)male in Malay television: The case of Senario", "created_at": "2018-12-10T18:46:08.659-08:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/37952673/Constituting_fe_male_in_Malay_television_The_case_of_Senario?f_ri=961759", "dom_id": "work_37952673", "summary": "This article examines the articulations of Malaysian Malay female identities as performed on Senario, Malaysia's longest produced sitcom. My close textual reading centres on the episode 'Dalam Hati Ada Taman' to identify three dimensions of female and gender constructions in Malay television; alternative constructions to traditional Malay female identities, negative portrayals of these non-traditional Malay females, and the incompatibility of non-Malay influences to traditional Malay female roles. The discussion demonstrates that all three function to reaffirm the resilience and rigidity of socially conceptualised notions of each mode of gender that are underpinned by more traditional understandings which are largely patriarchal. More broadly, the analysis foregrounds the slippage between dominant Malay social realities and screen media as well as the linkages between communal understandings of gender modes, and popularly interpreted notions of 'tradition' and/or 'culture'.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 57966891, "asset_id": 37952673, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 5512378, "first_name": "Luqman", "last_name": "Lee", "domain_name": "uuiioo", "page_name": "LuqmanLee", "display_name": "Luqman Lee", "profile_url": "https://uuiioo.academia.edu/LuqmanLee?f_ri=961759", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/5512378/6036094/58177580/s65_luqman.lee.png"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 696, "name": "Gender Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Gender_Studies?f_ri=961759", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 1571, "name": "Television Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Television_Studies?f_ri=961759", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 4917, "name": "Gender and Sexuality", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Gender_and_Sexuality?f_ri=961759", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 7024, "name": "Gender", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Gender?f_ri=961759", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 7490, "name": "Gender Equality", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Gender_Equality?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 11155, "name": "Women and Gender Issues in Islam", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Women_and_Gender_Issues_in_Islam?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 34074, "name": "Television", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Television?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 43965, "name": "Malaysian Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malaysian_Studies?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 96749, "name": "Sitcoms", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Sitcoms?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 340188, "name": "gender issues and Islamisation in Malaysia", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/gender_issues_and_Islamisation_in_Malaysia?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 723155, "name": "Malay Women", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malay_Women?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 737350, "name": "Effects of Sitcoms", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Effects_of_Sitcoms?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 961759, "name": "Indonesia and the Malay World", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Indonesia_and_the_Malay_World?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 1012083, "name": "TV Sitcoms", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/TV_Sitcoms?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 1015170, "name": "The Malay World", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/The_Malay_World?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 1561270, "name": "Malay Women Identities", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malay_Women_Identities?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 2937801, "name": "Malaysian Television", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malaysian_Television?f_ri=961759"}, {"id": 3031512, "name": "Malay Television", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malay_Television?f_ri=961759"}]}, {"id": 40528333, "title": "Abdul Samad Al-Falimbani's Role and Contribution in the Discourse of Islamic Knowledge in the Malay World", "created_at": "2019-10-04T23:19:43.464-07:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/40528333/Abdul_Samad_Al_Falimbanis_Role_and_Contribution_in_the_Discourse_of_Islamic_Knowledge_in_the_Malay_World?f_ri=961759", "dom_id": "work_40528333", "summary": "Abstract\nShaykh Abdussamad al-Falimbani was an important figure in the intellectual tradition of Islam in the Malay world in the 18th century. This article shows that al-Falimbani played an important role in conveying and developing Islamic sciences, not only in the Malay World even in Arab lands, including in Makkah and in Zabid, Yemen. Al-Falimbani was also one of the superior scholars who not only received recognition from fellow scholars and students from among the Malays, even from his colleagues and students who were Arab. Al-Falimbani's important contribution to the intellectual tradition of Islam in Malay World was: the first, the spread of al-Falimbani's various religious works to various regions of the Islamic world, both in Southeast Asia and the Middle East. Second, the development of intellectual networks of teachers and students in the region of Malay and Middle East in the 18th century. Third, the maintenance of the continuity of Islamic scientific treasures from the classical Islamic scholars to the Muslims in the 18th century even to the modern era today. Fourth, harmonize tasawuf teachings with Islamic law, so that the traditions and rituals of Sufism remain practiced in the corridors of the valid Shari'a.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 60802569, "asset_id": 40528333, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 4724774, "first_name": "Dr Mohammed Hussain", "last_name": "Ahmad", "domain_name": "independent", "page_name": "DrMohammedHussainAhmad", "display_name": "Dr Mohammed Hussain Ahmad", "profile_url": "https://independent.academia.edu/DrMohammedHussainAhmad?f_ri=961759", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/4724774/1997933/33405762/s65_dr_mohammed_hussain.ahmad.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 102363, "name": "Malay Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malay_Studies?f_ri=961759", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 158040, "name": "Malay-Indonesian Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malay-Indonesian_Studies?f_ri=961759", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 961753, "name": "Malay World Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malay_World_Studies?f_ri=961759", "nofollow": false}